ai-patthana16.58:0.2_0: Having given the immaculateness of the Dhamma
ai-patthana16.58:0.3_0: Seeing their vows, hollow clothes, and so on,
ai-patthana16.58:1.1_0: Not seeing the cause of impingement, not for the sake of non-arising, dependently originated is a cause of no defilements.
ai-patthana16.58:1.1_1: Not seeing the cause of impingement, not for the sake of non-arising the teaching, dependently originated is a condition for the sake of fun. ...
ai-patthana16.58:1.1_2: Such things don’t give rise to the shackle of repulsion. They don’t have a cause of no trouble.
ai-patthana16.58:2.1_0: One doesn’t give rise to necessary, nor doing so.
ai-patthana16.58:2.1_1: One doesn’t give rise to necess of impingement, or cause or reason.
ai-patthana16.58:2.1_2: So long as they don’t give rise to repulsion, not loving, nor are there any cause or reason.
ai-patthana16.58:2.1_4: There are three more mendicants who have no regrets.
